          "text": "Now I have enough information to compile a comprehensive security review. Here's my analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Security Review Summary\n\n### Critical Issues\n\n#### 1. **Hackathon Admin Auth Bypassed When API Key Not Set**\n**File:** `src/services/hackathon/authService.ts` (lines 6-9)\n\n```6:14:src/services/hackathon/authService.ts\n  if (!configuredKey) {\n    return;\n  }\n```\n\nIf `HACKATHON_ADMIN_API_KEY` is not configured, the function silently returns without throwing an error, effectively making all admin endpoints **publicly accessible**. This is a severe misconfiguration risk.\n\n**Fix:** Throw an error when the API key is not configured in production.\n\n---\n\n#### 2. **SSL Certificate Validation Disabled**\n**File:** `src/db/mikro-orm.config.ts` (line 12-14)\n\n```8:16:src/db/mikro-orm.config.ts\nexport default defineConfig({\n  entities: [User, HackathonSubmissionSession, HackathonProjectSubmission, CommunityProfile, CommunityEvent],\n  clientUrl: process.env.DATABASE_URL,\n  driverOptions: {\n    connection: {\n      ssl: { rejectUnauthorized: false },\n    },\n  },\n});\n```\n\n`rejectUnauthorized: false` disables SSL certificate verification, making the connection vulnerable to **man-in-the-middle attacks**. This should only be used for development.\n\n---\n\n### High Priority Issues\n\n#### 3. **Missing NEXTAUTH_SECRET Validation**\n**File:** `src/lib/auth.ts` (line 55)\n\n```55:55:src/lib/auth.ts\n  secret: process.env.NEXTAUTH_SECRET,\n```\n\nNo validation that `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` is set. If undefined, NextAuth may use a default or predictable secret, compromising JWT token security.\n\n---\n\n#### 4. **Unauthenticated Hackathon Submission Endpoint (POST)**\n**File:** `src/app/api/hackathon/sessions/[token]/submissions/route.ts` (lines 26-58)\n\nThe `POST` handler for creating submissions does **not require admin authentication** - anyone with a valid session token can submit. While the token acts as a form of authorization, tokens are:\n- Exposed in URLs/QR codes\n- Never expire after the session end date\n- Predictable if someone can guess the 48-character hex format\n\nThis may be intentional, but consider adding rate limiting.\n\n---\n\n#### 5. **No Rate Limiting**\nMultiple endpoints lack rate limiting:\n- Registration endpoint (`/api/auth/register`)\n- Login via NextAuth credentials\n- Hackathon submissions\n- File uploads\n\nThis allows brute-force attacks, credential stuffing, and resource exhaustion.\n\n---\n\n#### 6. **File Upload Extension Bypass Potential**\n**File:** `src/app/api/upload/route.ts` (lines 38-39)\n\n```38:39:src/app/api/upload/route.ts\n  const ext = file.name.split(\".\").pop() || \"png\";\n  const objectKey = `uploads/${crypto.randomUUID()}.${ext}`;\n```\n\nThe file extension comes from user input (`file.name`). While MIME type is validated, a mismatch like `malicious.html` with `image/png` MIME could still be stored with `.html` extension, potentially enabling XSS if the bucket serves files directly.\n\n**Fix:** Derive extension from the validated MIME type, not the filename.\n\n---\n\n### Medium Priority Issues\n\n#### 7. **No Middleware for Route Protection**\nNo `middleware.ts` file exists. All auth checks are done per-route, increasing the risk of missing protection on new routes. Consider implementing centralized middleware.\n\n---\n\n#### 8. **Weak Password Policy**\n**File:** `src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts` (lines 17-22)\n\n```17:22:src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts\n  if (password.length < 6) {\n    return NextResponse.json(\n      { error: \"Password must be at least 6 characters\" },\n      { status: 400 }\n    );\n  }\n```\n\n6 characters is weak. No complexity requirements (uppercase, numbers, symbols).\n\n---\n\n#### 9. **No Input Length Limits**\nVarious endpoints accept string inputs without maximum length validation:\n- `eventName`, `projectName`, `team`, `description` fields\n- Could lead to database storage issues or DoS\n\n---\n\n#### 10. **Token Enumeration Possible**\n**File:** `src/app/api/hackathon/sessions/[token]/status/route.ts`\n\nThe `/status` endpoint is unauthenticated and reveals whether a token exists. Attackers could enumerate valid tokens.\n\n---\n\n### Low Priority / Best Practices\n\n#### 11. **No CORS Configuration**\n`next.config.ts` has no explicit CORS headers. API routes may be callable from any origin.\n\n---\n\n#### 12. **Error Messages Could Leak Info**\n- \"Email already registered\" in `/api/auth/register` enables email enumeration\n- Session not found vs. invalid token errors could help attackers\n\n---\n\n#### 13. **Missing Security Headers**\nNo CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, etc. configured in Next.js config.\n\n---\n\n### Recommendations Summary\n\n| Priority | Issue | Recommendation |\n|----------|-------|----------------|\n| **Critical** | Admin bypass when no API key | Throw error if `HACKATHON_ADMIN_API_KEY` is not set in production |\n| **Critical** | SSL disabled | Enable `rejectUnauthorized: true` in production |\n| **High** | Missing NEXTAUTH_SECRET check | Validate secret exists at startup |\n| **High** | No rate limiting | Add rate limiting (e.g., `@upstash/ratelimit`) |\n| **High** | File extension from user input | Use MIME-to-extension mapping |\n| **Medium** | No middleware | Add centralized auth middleware |\n| **Medium** | Weak password policy | Require 8+ chars, complexity |\n| **Medium** | No input length limits | Add max length validation |\n| **Low** | Missing security headers | Configure in `next.config.ts` |\n| **Low** | Email enumeration | Use generic \"invalid credentials\" messages |\n\nWould you like me to implement fixes for any of these issues?",
